
[1]wholesale

   WHOLESALE, n. [whole and sale.]

   1. Sale of goods by the piece or large quantity; as distinguished from
   retail. Some traders sell either by wholesale or retail.

   2. The whole mass.

   Some from vanity or envy, despise a valuable book, and throw contempt
   upon it by wholesale.

                           WHOLESALE, a. [supra.]

   1. Buying and selling by the piece or quantity; as a wholesale merchant
   or dealer.

   2. Pertaining to the trade by the piece or quantity; as the wholesale
   price.
